modules.description: Provides functions to check, convert, and manipulate exit status values derived from C's stdlib.h. It operates on integers representing system exit codes and includes utilities for translating between numeric values and symbolic representations. Use it to handle process termination statuses in command-line applications or system scripts.

Provides functions to generate success or failure exit values, with `success` returning a value of any type upon successful termination and `failure` doing the same for errors. Works with integers for exit codes and a boolean to indicate POSIX compliance. Used to signal program outcomes in command-line tools and system scripts.
